            // Module: Investing Primer (formerly Women and the Collective: Investing)
            Module(
                id: "mod_women",
                title: "Investing Primer",
                description: "Exploring women's unique approach to investing, collective strategies, and building financial confidence.",
                icon: "💪",
                color: "blue",
                heroImageName: "hero_women",
                sections: [
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_women_1",
                        title: "Align your Investments with your Purpose_",
                        content: [
                            .text("This theme will cover the ideas, concepts, materials and discovery process of women and investing. This is a taste of the Literacy Modules offered, but if you, our platform guest, take one thing away from this quick module it is this:"),
                            .text("In today's culture more women need to be at the forefront of wealth creation. In our post-modern capitalistic society, the structural set up is Money = Power = Choice. Women need the Freedom of Choice, the Liberty of Autonomy and the Capital Infrastructure to have the opportunity to make innovative change for self and within society. "),
                            .callout(title: "Key Terms", content: "Investing Terminology ", type: .info)
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_women_2",
                        title: "Who we Are vs. Why we are Here_",
                        content: [
                            .text("For you to embrace your place, your own financial and holistic ecosystem, first embrace your own power of choice.  "),
                            .callout(title: "Historical Perspective", content: "Never before in the history of humankind have women had such a megaphone for personal choice, yet the structures offered to us, particularly the financial models given, reflect a poor optimization of our Voice and our Power.", type: .info),
                            .text("Before you start, recognize that this journey, your financial journey, does not need a complete overhaul, rather small tweaks along the way. If you get to a path that is unfamiliar keep walking, testing each stone you might have to balance on. The footing is there, it might just need some reinforcement. And remember, you are not alone on this adventure. "),
                            .text("One area in financial empowerment is the understanding of asset allocation. Having an overall vision of where you want to go, theoretically, can help you determine the best entry points for investing. Having multiple financial assets working on your behalf is an important, yet easily overlooked component to financial freedom. And it brings about the opportunity of choice."),
                            .text("Consider the narratives you have been told about wealth. Consider what ecosystems you have found yourself within concerning your financial future. Consider if you find it possible to dive into a new thought process concerning wealth creation. If so, you are in the right place!"),
                            .text("First, let us look at our own personal power to wield such choices with the wisdom to navigate the options that are best suited for our goals. ")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_women_3",
                        title: "1. Power_",
                        content: [
                            .heading("1.1 The Myth, The Snowflake and The Data Drivers", level: 3),
                            .text("💨 The Myth"),
                            .text("There have been many myths over centuries that have defined both social and interpersonal factors around women and finances. "),
                            .text("Notice I did not write \"investing,” because first we need to break down the foundational myths that we, as a collective society, have embedded into our psyche around the natural interests, barriers and ownership of money. "),
                            .text("❄️ The Snowflake"),
                            .text("We are conditioned to accept (unknowingly or begrudgingly) others definitions of us. This happens in every aspect of life, but shows itself most in the area of 💰. From here on out, consider your emerging individuality, especially in connection to your financial future. "),
                            .text("Genetically, we are all unique creatures with the same foundational structure. Our ability to pattern match, future project and navigate systems, both natural and man-made, allows for our capacity to build the life that we desire. While we are made up of the same form, we show up in the world incredibly diverse and individualized. "),
                            .text("Within the workforce, women have different career trajectories, goals and retirement needs. If you are outside the traditional workforce, then your needs are even more specialized. I understand. I have been in both scenarios. "),
                            .text("Like cattle calls, being evaluated with distinct and unjust historical biases, we get plugged into a broken system. Then when moments of failure come about we become a working example of those broken systems. A mirror. These broken examples reflect mass social and infrastructure failings projected onto the female investor. "),
                            .text("It is better to move away from a binary thought process of (+-) to an intuitive ecosystem. By that statement I am suggesting we look at multiple factors in financial wellness, outside of just money in/money out.  "),
                            .text("Studied in both Rich Dad, Poor Dad and the Psychology of Money, there are parts of our upbringing, observations and networks that influence our decision making. In the past 15 years, the Millennial generation have faced both the Financial Crisis of '08 and the Covid Pandemic. Gen X had 9/11. Gen Z is moving into an even more unknown and unwritten future."),
                            .text("The way our parents and grandparents navigated wealth creation and financial growth does not exist in the same way for current investors. Many of the financial products that brought down the banks in '08-09, the sub-prime mortgage crisis, were created in the 1970's. (1) The ability to wrap high value financial products into junk bonds for consumers to purchase brought about a chilling and complex domino effect. The post-war boom that our parents generation was born into no longer exists. The importance of our current financial markets is learning to navigate what is currently being offered, new products on the market, and how to best utilized the latest regulatory and technological changes. Its a new era- one that has the ability to be prosperous. The rules of this new terrain are currently being written.  "),
                            .heading("1.2 The Brain and Money", level: 3),
                            .text("Outside of learned behavior, neuroscientists and psychologists have found that people do not always behave the way economists' describe. "),
                            .text("Within the study of Neuroeconomics, (yes, that is a thing!) Dr. Jonathan Cohen, the co-director at the Princeton Neuroscience Institute breaks down two terms in decision making: \"deliberative\" and \"emotional.” He describes the seemingly subtle differences but are acutely fundamental in the decision making process. (2)"),
                            .text("To break it down, here are excerpts condensed for clarification: "),
                            .text("If you want to jump down the rabbit hole of Evolutionary Brain Development in conjunction with Current Economic Theory: dive in below... 👇 (2.1)"),
                            .text("Issues arise, especially in the context of resources. Meaning, different parts of our brain have adapted to different types of circumstances. Currently there is not a control structure that knows the most appropriate choice in any given circumstances. There is not a full optimization- yet we have to make \"such choices all the time.”"),
                            .text("It is important to know when we come up to making choices that are best for us, especially in investing, we are able to recognize we are making the best choices we have at that moment. "),
                            .text("Due to the advancements of technology, (and the \"scrolling effect\") we are now given endless choices with variant outcomes. "),
                            .text("The concept of \"analysis paralysis\" is not new, but can be overwhelming given we have few ways to properly filter our options. "),
                            .text("This is why it is important to develop skills from the neuro-economic terms above. "),
                            .divider,
                            .heading("💫 New Ways Forward_", level: 3),
                            .callout(title: "Intuition vs Reaction", content: "Moving forward, my theory is to utilize your intuition versus “gut” reaction. ", type: .tip),
                            .text("Due to the nature and slight inadequacy of the terminology of “gut” reaction in our society and business dealings. Very few use this specific term to navigate from a neuro-economic basis, rather it evokes an incorrect colloquial understanding.  "),
                            .text("The idea of perfection will not help in this situation. Using the above terminology can help create a sound observation around one's own process. And the key to this journey is to learn how to fully trust one’s own investing process. "),
                            .heading("The Why_", level: 3),
                            .text("It is vital to understand how individuals process information. In a usually complex topic such as money and investments, it is important to assert we can navigate the dense historical, familial and hierarchal dynamics of wealth. "),
                            .text("You might have heard the lines, “Its just money”, \"Money is just energy\" and \"Just direct the energy\" it is a radically oversimplification of an historically bankrupt structure that has deep ties and steep consequences for women. "),
                            .text("While money is a tool, it is imperative to account how much more women as a gender have had to overcome to even come close to the \"idea\" of meritocracy. "),
                            .heading("1.3 Recover your Power_", level: 3),
                            .text("😳 Navigating the current “Full Blown Crisis”, grappling with economic and societal Fears"),
                            .text("The term Fear covers a variety of categories within this context. Outside the concept of the fear of the future, of instability within investment accounts, global climate change- all of the categories we have only a small control of personal accountability; let us dispel the pejorative qualities that have been conveyed in conjunction to women and finances. "),
                            .callout(title: "Common Misconceptions", content: "Examples of Societal Projections: \n1. A One-Size-Fits all Approach.\n2. Women are afraid to take financial risks.\n3. Women are uninterested in investing. ", type: .tip),
                            .text("Let us state this as clearly as possible- the fear around your ability to invest, in all aspects, should be countered within the proper framework of facts, not societal projections. "),
                            .text("There may be feelings of vulnerability or unease. This is a road you are just beginning. The edges of the path are not well worn. Know though, you have the ability, wherewithal and functionality* to navigate. "),
                            .text("Elizabeth Gilbert spoke on the concept of \"no fear\" being for sociopaths. We all need a healthy amount of fear. It keeps us alive, keeps us aware and keeps us moving forward. "),
                            .text("Remember, healthy fear is based on the truth of the actual situation, not blind faith that all things will magically work out. "),
                            .text("The domino effect mentioned in the previous section, is where we live today. With the Great Recession came an incredible change in how we build the long-term structures of our lives. The financial crisis of '08, includes decreases in fertility. (4; 5) Women of the Millennial generation have been navigating the basic challenges this crisis sparked, including delaying home buying along with starting a family. Many have recovered, but those years marked significant losses. Now with Covid we will only see the full fall out in the years to come, including the increase of first time parents but the decision to not have anymore children for families with multiple children. (6) At the time of this final edit our markets and crypto have become linked in a volatile downturn and talks of another Recession is looming. (7)"),
                            .text("Due to the recognition of institutional gaslighting within finance, one major change that has allowed positive action: more women are aware and active in their own financial wellness. "),
                            .divider,
                            .text("💾 The Data Drivers"),
                            .text("A study by Merrill Lynch in partnership with Age Wave surveyed women around this topic. (8)"),
                            .callout(title: "The Data: Women & Investing", content: "41% — Biggest financial regret is not investing more.\n59% — Report they are not doing a good job using investing as a tool for their financial goals.\n60% — Cite not having the knowledge base to invest as their #1 barrier.\n34% — Cite not having enough confidence.", type: .keyPoint),
                            .callout(title: "Values-Based Investing", content: "Women want their relationship with money to be linked to their values, goals and priorities.", type: .info),
                            .divider,
                            .heading("Financial Embodiment_", level: 3),
                            .text("The term \"Embodiment\" is a great avenue for personal integration. Financial wellness is imperative to navigate all the twists and turns life offers. It provides a point of preparation as life unfolds. "),
                            .text("Over the course of your financial embodiment there are a few key questions to consider outside of your overall goal: "),
                            .callout(title: "Self-Assessment", content: "Question One: What is my Baseline Readiness? \nQuestion Two: What is my Baseline Resilience? ", type: .info),
                            .text("Baseline readiness and baseline resilience are terms more known in the disaster preparedness circles. These tools allow you to consider and prepare for future outcomes. Perceiving both positive and/or negative results, allowing for multiple scenarios. This can curb any inherent anxiety in relationship to money. It can bring peace of mind."),
                            .text("It comes from the fact that you took the time to observe, plan and act."),
                            .text("There is great power here and personal stewardship that brings about autonomy during states of crisis."),
                            .text("When considering your future:"),
                            .callout(title: "Planning Questions", content: "How do you want it to look? \nHow do you value your time? \nWhat stages should you put money aside for travel, education, a home, retirement, or to possibly start a company or passion project? ", type: .info),
                            .heading("Personal Agency_", level: 3),
                            .text("Integral investing, one of personal agency, is recovering or uncovering your sense of Power. Especially for women, the topic of money, finances and economic empowerment is mixed with a complex history around the roles and value of women. More than spreadsheets and data points, psychology plays a massive role in how you interact with money. "),
                            .text("In the generalization of investing, the typical advice is \"invest in what you know.\" "),
                            .text("Currently products on the market, working with both a financial advisor* and/or on your own using a trading app, it is hard to decipher, know and navigate the way ETFs and stocks are purchased and sold. How then are you able to follow the age old advice? Women in general prefer to think long term. Sallie Krawcheck of Ellevest has brought attention to this subject, both to the public and the powers that be, who decide and create the financial products currently on the market. "),
                            .text("Since there is such a disconnect, no wonder women naturally feel misaligned. According to a study on behavioral economics and decision making with Americans' savings decisions, there is a role around the need of clearly defined actions as well as easy to understand products. "),
                            .text("Beryl Chang writes on the subject in the paper, Nudges and Behavioral Economics, around the natural biases and limitations. "),
                            .text("It is also important to recognize unconscious gender biases within the investing space. Studies conducted by a joint study with the Yale School of Management and Columbia Business School shed light on the double standard women in the financial industry face even when objective information based on performance is at play. (10) In the The Motley Fool “Investors Like Me” Series point out that since there are fewer visible women in the investment space, it can contribute to a lack of confidence. (11)"),
                            .heading("So what does that all mean for us? ", level: 3),
                            .text("Simply put, as humans, we try and make the best decisions with the best information we have at that moment. Our brains are naturally trained, both consciously and unconsciously to keep us out of danger. As we allow ourselves new ways of learning, exploring and being available to adjust we are able to navigate those inherited biases or our natural protective systems. Such is why it is best to incrementally grow and why investing is a positive way to allow for periods of growth, integration and hedge moments of downturn- ie real life 🏹 🙌🤦‍♀️."),
                            .text("It is important to recognize that gender bias plays a role. The act of seeing a visual representation in the industry is an important confidence booster for female investors. "),
                            .text("Though, when the term \"go with your gut\" is used, in a way, learning to invest in what you know coupled with your own internal intuitive process allows for greater success. Having an attitude and knowledge that, usually, most things do not go as planned, but adjusting along the way will allow sanity to be maintained."),
                            .callout(title: "Key Formula", content: "👉 Money = Power = Choice", type: .info),
                            .text("Remember money is a tool. For many, this statement is a difficult one to process. In part because our societal structures tie our financial outcomes with our internal worth. Psychologically, our mind repeat and reflect this patterning. For some, money becomes intertwined with their identity. "),
                            .callout(title: "Mindset Shift", content: "Money is a tool. Your worth is inherently different. Repeat this out loud if necessary. ", type: .info),
                            .text("In a separate module offering we dive deeper into Behavioral Economics. It drives the entitreity of our financial future, as well as the studies found around both conscious and unconscious biases in the space."),
                            .heading("1.4 Lies, Money and the Female Empowerment Endgame", level: 3),
                            .text("At the final edits of this module, there has been an ever increased, dare to say, war on women. At seemingly every step of especially these last few years, women's rights that were hard won are getting chipped away- both publicly and privately. In a capitalistic society, especially in the US, your dollar is your vote. Look around, notice how money moves in and around industries, cities, brands and families. "),
                            .text("In considering the complex dynamics around finances, investing, inheritances and even taxes, many emotions rise. "),
                            .callout(title: "Reflection", content: "How does this make you feel?", type: .info),
                            .text("Sometimes the answers come quickly. Sometimes they take a bit of probing. This probing we will address fully in later modules. "),
                            .localImage(name: "feelings_wheel", caption: "Look at the feelings chart to begin considering through what lens this topic is viewed. Remember, there are no incorrect answers. Truth is a shift that allows change to take place."),
                            .text("To see again economic upheaval, unfairly hitting women full force, is unconscionable. Consider what emotion may be your catalyst for personal sovereignty in your financial health. Make your Truth your fuel to move your life and the world around you forward. "),
                            .divider,
                            .text("How your Financial Path Started:"),
                            .text("Now, more than ever, with the incredible technological, innovative and creative ways to navigate the everyday, is it important to first look at how you started your financial path.  "),
                            .callout(title: "Money Context", content: "In the context of money: ", type: .info),
                            .text("\nShame: "),
                            .text("This subject deserves an entire book, but it is a touchpoint worth mentioning. It is a factor in how humans grow their financial future. Women especially have been in an unyielding dynamic when it comes to value, money and financial caretaking. "),
                            .text("At one point or another, you might have felt shame around wealth. Shame is different than guilt. As Brene Brown has so eloquently shifted our understanding, guilt implies you did something wrong. Shame implies you are inherently wrong. It is common for shame to unconsciously navigate your life choices. As some point it becomes imperative to recognize these points and use them as a catalyst for change. "),
                            .text("It is important to make space for shame. Instead of denying factors that are leading our decision making processes, either consciously or unconsciously, we can be kinder and gentler to our internal navigation systems. And eventually to others. "),
                            .text("Since we can learn from all parts of the human experience, shame can point us to the areas of our life where we are out of alignment or simply off course with our value system and/or where we have behaved in ways that are out of integrity with ourselves. "),
                            .text("🙌🏽 Joy:"),
                            .text("Enjoy the investing process; let this spark a sense of adventure. Instead of thinking of investing as a Zero-Sum Game, move into the mindset of a Positive Sum Game. By viewing investing in the mindset of Positive Sum, you are recognizing that there are multiple opportunities to grow your long term wealth. If one is not best suited for you, then begin anew. "),
                            .text("Your background informs but does not have to define your future. As women are becoming more passionate around financial wellness- in part for personal power and for many certain necessities. There have historically been much greater and steeper mountains for many of us, especially women, have had to climb to achieve some semblance of financial peace. The myth of meritocracy still reigns, but when we recognize our part we break the power of this potent American myth. We to have the ability to create the financial health and wealth we so desire for ourselves and our family."),
                            .text("Many women are small business owners. In a very true sense they invested in themselves, in their own company. "),
                            .text("What happens when you actually succeed in your financial gains? What then? "),
                            .callout(title: "Questions to Consider", content: "A few questions to consider: \nWho do you look to or turn to in order to maximize the longer term wealth creation? \nWhat are the tax implications of your growth? \n\n(Further exploration is in our 💸 Principles_ Tools_ Possibility Section for members.)", type: .info),
                            .heading("Opportunity for Embodiment_", level: 3),
                            .text("Own what you want. Yes, the physical items that you will buy with money, but truly the emotion of building your own financial stability, security and well crafted life. Own how you perceive yourself in your worth. "),
                            .text("These are big questions with big implications. The more economically strong women are as a group, the more of a holistic planet we can build. This is not a utopian vision, rather detailed and proven out statements. When money is the hands of women, they create better working environments, better investment decisions, grow companies in a financially sound way. They are able to provide for their children, take care of themselves, their own mental energy and the overall safety of their community."),
                            .divider,
                            .heading("Discussion_", level: 3),
                            .text("You and Investing:"),
                            .callout(title: "Questions to Consider", content: "\nWithin the context of investing:", type: .info),
                            .divider
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_women_4",
                        title: "2. Current Social Structures_",
                        content: [
                            .text("Writer Catherine Lacey sums it up well when she writes:"),
                            .quote("“Women so often carry this delusion of being innately wrong, of needing to be numbed, controlled, caged or hidden — a delusion smuggled into us in the Trojan horse of a thousand old stories.” ", author: nil),
                            .text("In the context of our current social structures, one may feel the weight of personal responsibility outweighs the relevance of systematic biases. While it is important to live in a place of radical responsibility it would be an injustice to not voice such delusions. "),
                            .text("It is important to clearly state that there are systems of oppression, injustice, marginalization and institutional abuse outside of your control. You deserve access to financial instruments that allow for financial safety, freedom and most of all respect. "),
                            .heading("2.1 Your Current State_", level: 3),
                            .text("If possible, aim to let go of the mindset that there is only one specific process for investing. There are multiple avenues to the same goal. Financial freedom and long term wealth being the journey. You may have the finances to invest from your income, other portfolio contributions, alimony, divorce or an inheritance. Many women step into wealth through the unfortunate event of becoming a widow. Other women have access to family money, that through the power and fortitude of generations past.  "),
                            .text("Many have been in the workforce since their teens- navigating corporate life and structures that make it difficult to naturally grow their wealth when they are making $0.80 on the dollar (12) . Several have gone down the route of entrepreneurship and own their own business. As of 2019, 42% of businesses and firms were owned by women making up a larger portion of market share. One in five firms with revenue of $1M or more is female-owned. (13) \n"),
                            .quote("“The potential of women entrepreneurs for spurring economic growth has not been fully realized”._ State of Women-Owned Business Report by American Express; 2019", author: nil),
                            .text("Bloomberg recently shed light on a survey that found almost half of 2021’s new entrepreneurs were women. Leading to a 28% increase from 2019. (14) This is in part why Untitled_ exists. To serve you. We know that historically the banking industry has been incredibly difficult to navigate on multiple levels. "),
                            .text("Many are now in the position to make true dividends from their hard work, income stream and asset allocations. "),
                            .text("It is important to recognize that we all get to this path in one way or another, but it is vital to own it. It is your path and your birthright. The goal is to navigate longer-term financial growth with confidence and ease. The last thing women need is the burden of institutional neglect and irresponsibility of asset management. ")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_women_5",
                        title: "3. Modern Day Legal and Social Structures_",
                        content: [
                            .heading(" 🏹", level: 3),
                            .heading("3.1 The 20th Century_", level: 3),
                            .text("In the 20th Century, outside of the Industrial Revolution that found many women and children in the workforce, a large portion of economic progress was the expansion of the West. "),
                            .text("From the East Coast of New England to the Western Plains into California, the drive to grow was pushed by American ingenuity, innovation and the pioneer. It was the 1839 Married Women’s Property Acts that allowed women to own property, engage in business and legally keep their income. (15) This was a key passage that became a foundational shift stating women were no longer their husband’s property, nor did all of their inheritance and property automatically become their spouses. Yet, it was still not commonly practiced. Small family and women owned businesses allowed for greater wealth expansion for the American economy. "),
                            .text("Unlike their European counterparts, vast growth was established by land grabs. From an artistic perspective though, the great artists of that time were still coming from Europe. "),
                            .text("In most to all varied circumstances, power and financial decisions were few and far between for women. This set the stage of where we are currently. "),
                            .text("The fact that women were not even included in the United States Constitution as citizens pulls at the difficult dynamic American women have faced. In her letters to her husband, Abigail Adams contributes perspective that was eventually ignored, but shows the need for women to have equanimity. "),
                            .text("Women have historically built the American Economy, through both paid and unpaid labor, but until very recently had little options to determine their own economic fate. "),
                            .text("Even as the Industrial Revolution brought great financial power to the United States women were not given the opportunity to cast their vote, the only structure for representation, until 1920 when the Nineteenth Amendment become ratified. "),
                            .text("Globally the United Nations General Assembly adopted the Convention on Political Rights of Women in 1954 codified a basic standard for women’s political rights. "),
                            .text("Why bring this up?"),
                            .text("Well, it is important to recognize our current financial structures and institutions actually were born in this era. Take JP Morgan/Chase, Barclays, Citi (Citicorp) and Bank of America (Massachusetts Bank) were founded and operating durning this period.(16-18) It’s hard to imagine that multi-national banking conglomerates, in their formation, were family run businesses. The industrial revolution set the foundation for how, in part, our financial infrastructure still operates. "),
                            .text("So imagine for a minute, all the social, political, and for these purposes, economic forces at play during the turn of the century. The battle for equality, voting rights, access to education and the power to decide one's path in this world is colliding. These are the dynamics that are the underpinnings of our current economic and financial infrastructure. The rails of our financial products rest in this upheaval. "),
                            .callout(title: "Art Market Note", content: "Art Market Side Note: Most of the artworks created during this time up unto the late 80's have had a profound effect on the art market. Each work receiving higher and higher valuations. Post-war artists, first supported by the New Deal initiatives with the WPA allowed for massive public works through the Depression, to artists who were able to come back from the war on the GI Bill, broke open the American Economy. (19)", type: .tip),
                            .heading("3.2 Mid Century", level: 3),
                            .text("This time frame in history is significant for us today. To truly understand our place in the context of this we must look at the place women represented in history. "),
                            .text("In the 1950/60s industrialization made goods cheaper, quicker and automated. The Post-War Boom brought many economic benefits to the American way of life. Women were pursuing education, but few were allowed to fully flex those muscles in the work force. "),
                            .text("For women during this period there was a general unnamed malaise. Once identified it turned into frustration, part historical rebellion and a general demand for systematic reforms."),
                            .text("In the seminal work, The Feminine Mystique by Betty Friedan, "),
                            .text("Friedan points out that through history, men have been able to write and control their destinies. Traditionally, finances were a man’s game and women were relegated to the outskirts of society, far from power, and far from having the pleasure of dictating laws, regulations, business and industries that affected their daily lives."),
                            .text("Many of you felt the effects of 2008. All you have to do is watch the Big Short to get an introduction into the domino effect of how Mortgage Backed Securities brought an entire industry to its knees. This financial product was first brought to market in 1968. (21) Many other financial products utilized today have the same blueprint of as those securities. "),
                            .text("From the late 1970’s to 2020 American Business and Industry has radically changed. This is in part due to significant deregulation starting in the Carter Administration and continuing with the Regan Administration. Our current understanding of capitalism and free-market economics promoted by Nobel laureate Milton Friedman made waves within our government, moving away from the thinking of Roosevelts’ New Deal. The majority of the Securities and Exchange Commission regulations were formed in 1934. (22) "),
                            .text("In fact, Untitled_ falls under the ‘34 Security’s Reg D 506c Act. During the Obama administration, in order to update laws and promote larger access to financial products, including alternative assets, the SEC included Regulation Crowdfunding (CF) and Regulation A. As of November 2020, a new set of regulatory laws were passed to lower the threshold of “accredited” investors as well as broaden the amounts companies are able to raise. (23)"),
                            .text("In many ways regulations have been updated to protect both consumers and the industry by the introduction of the Frank-Dodd Act. Hopefully there will continue to be a balance within the financial system to offset another Black Swan event again. "),
                            .heading("3.3 Here we are now...", level: 3),
                            .text("In the context of today, we have the world's wealthiest men competing with each other as to who will beat each other into outer space. Like the late 60's that led into the 2nd wave of feminism in the 70's, we have a cultural reckoning.  In the wake of the reverberations of multiple cultural movements, there is still much work to be done. Not only in the hands of women, but in the founders of the startups who will serve these women. If we can, in essence, demand more from our services, especially those that happily take our money, those needs will be better met. One way or another. "),
                            .text("Women as a whole understand the needs of the collective. Of society. Of future generations. The reworking of society to include all. "),
                            .text("A McKinsey study called for interventions to address attitudinal biases. (24)"),
                            .text("The call to action is palpable, and we at Untitled_ want to be a major stakeholder in financial services, with your help, trust and accountability. "),
                            .text("As stated, it is important to repeat once again, this historical reference point has only served, as stated, a very narrow female demographic. Our sisters that come from different races, places and social structures have not had the same opportunities. Only now, as a society, we are beginning to lock arms and support women collectively so that all have the opportunity to flourish. Though there is still a long way to go. "),
                            .text("Every woman needs to read A Timeline of Women’s Legal History in the United States by Stanford Law Professor Cunnea. It is a thorough and broad understanding of the legal components within the United States Legislation. "),
                            .text("Human history is complex. So is being a woman. May this be taken with the hope that there is a better way forward. A better future. A unique offering for more to be involved to evolve their own dignity, power and freedom. "),
                            .text("Now, more than ever, we need to rebuild and retool financial instruments that meet the needs of all, not just the few. Technology and updated laws and regulation within the Securities and Exchange Commission now allows for a clear, optimized and financially healthy solution. "),
                            .divider,
                            .callout(title: "Key Laws", content: "See the Key Laws tab for a timeline of legislation shaping women's economic and civic rights.", type: .info)
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_women_7",
                        title: "5. What Alternatives Are Not — And How to Think About Risk_",
                        content: [
                            .text("Before you invest in any alternative asset, a clear-eyed accounting of what they are not will serve you better than any enthusiasm about returns."),
                            .heading("5.1 A Fair Accounting_", level: 3),
                            .bulletList([
                                "Not fully liquid. Unlike stocks, you often can't exit on short notice. Some investments lock up your capital for 5–10 years.",
                                "Not simple to evaluate. Valuing a private company or a piece of art requires knowledge and due diligence that stocks don't demand.",
                                "Not unregulated. Most professional alternative investment managers are registered with the SEC — but due diligence on your part is still essential.",
                                "Not right for everyone at every stage. Alternatives typically make sense once you have an emergency fund, no high-interest debt, and some traditional market exposure."
                            ]),
                            .callout(title: "The Right Frame", content: "Alternative assets are a complement to a financial foundation, not a replacement for one. Most financial advisors suggest alternatives as 10–30% of a total portfolio, layered on top of traditional market exposure.", type: .tip),
                            .heading("5.2 How to Think About Your Own Risk Tolerance_", level: 3),
                            .text("Before investing in any alternative asset, honest answers to three questions will tell you most of what you need to know:"),
                            .numberedList([
                                "Time horizon: When might I need this money? If the answer is \"within 5 years,\" most alternatives are not appropriate.",
                                "Liquidity needs: Could I survive financially if this money was locked up and inaccessible? If not, liquidity risk is too high.",
                                "Knowledge: Do I understand how this asset makes money, what could go wrong, and how I would exit? If not, more research is needed before investing."
                            ]),
                            .statistic(value: "~3%", label: "Private equity annual outperformance over public markets (20-yr avg)", context: "Cambridge Associates, McKinsey Global Private Markets Report 2024")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: ["reflect_women_5"],
                        glossaryTerms: ["Liquidity", "Due Diligence", "Illiquidity Premium", "Risk-Adjusted Return"],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                ],
                reflectionPrompts: [],
                quizzes: [],
                caseStudies: [],
                estimatedTime: 45,
                tags: []
            ),

            // Module: Decentralized Finance
            Module(
                id: "mod_defi",
                title: "Decentralized Finance",
                description: "Understanding DeFi, blockchain technology, and the future of decentralized financial systems.",
                icon: "🔗",
                color: "blue",
                heroImageName: "hero_defi",
                sections: [
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_defi_1",
                        title: "A little bit utopian meets a little bit utilitarian…",
                        content: [
                            .callout(title: "Critical Insight", content: "The building of DeFi without representation is the next great wealth gap.", type: .info)
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_defi_2",
                        title: "1. DeFi 101: The Basics",
                        content: [
                            .text("Decentralized Finance describes a financial system that operates on blockchain technology and aims to recreate and improve upon traditional financial services in a decentralized manner."),
                            .text("\"DeFi,\" short for Decentralized Finance, represents dynamic and evolving mechanisms within the blockchain space. "),
                            .text("In a broader sense, it constitutes a category of decentralized applications (DApps) designed for financial services, underpinned by blockchain technology. "),
                            .text("DeFi encompasses a diverse array of technologies, business models, and organizational structures, with the overarching goal of replacing traditional intermediaries. DeFi transactions primarily involve digital assets and typically operate on top of foundational settlement platforms. "),
                            .text("DeFi is orchestrating tectonic shifts within the global financial edifice. In an era where the crypto and digital asset domain is hurtling through transformation, organizations find themselves at the crossroads of a remarkable opportunity, armed with the potential to reimagine their future business paradigms."),
                            .text("Despite the ever-evolving nature of digital assets and the regulatory landscape that enfolds DeFi, recent regulatory pronouncements and declarations have signaled a mounting focus on this arena. Regulatory bodies grapple with the surging tide of both retail and institutional adoption, and this surge begs the question of whether forthcoming regulatory endeavors could cast their shadow on potential opportunities. This backdrop underscores the need for a cautious and informed approach to DeFi within the broader context of digital assets. (1)"),
                            .text("Understanding the fundamentals of distributed ledger technology (DLT) is straightforward, even though the technology itself can be more intricate. DLT essentially involves creating a shared, unchangeable, and time-sequenced log of transactions. In simple terms, it's akin to a database that permits various entities, be they countries or organizations, to enter and update a continuous ledger. Imagine it as a constantly accessible transaction log, where every user must reach a consensus to record each new transaction. Once a transaction is verified and inscribed on the ledger, no participant can tamper with its historical record. (2)"),
                            .callout(title: "DApps", content: "Decentralized Applications", type: .tip),
                            .heading("🧊 1.1 Web3 and Ownership_", level: 3),
                            .text("The term Web3 has been thrown around the cultural lexicon as of late. In basic terms Web3 is best described below:"),
                            .text("Web1- “Read Only”. "),
                            .text("The early days of the internet, previous to the dot-com bubble mainly consisted of webpages that were read only. If you were the owner and/or programer you could input the info as you built it out. "),
                            .text("Web2- “Read and Write” "),
                            .text("Through the inventions of third party platforms such as Facebook, Twitter. These platforms allowed users to create and add their own content to the platform. When a user did create, the platform itself, the gateway to it all, made money off the users content.  "),
                            .text("Web3- “Read, Write and Own”"),
                            .text("Through the use of Decentralized Networks versus centralized servers, users are now in control of their own data. Users can be fully in control of anything and everything they create. As a tech driven society the use of Web3 will naturally evolve what we think the economy should look like. It will facilitate the way we build companies. With this new found ability of direct ownership a sense of stewardship and a purpose built direction will be allowed at the beginning of projects. "),
                            .heading("🧨 1.2 DeFi Powered by Blockchain_", level: 3),
                            .text("At the heart of decentralized finance (DeFi) lies the dynamic duo of blockchain and cryptocurrency, the core technologies that breathe life into this financial revolution."),
                            .text("In the conventional financial world, your everyday transactions are securely recorded in a private ledger—your personal banking history. This ledger is owned and managed by a major financial institution. Now, imagine a decentralized, distributed public ledger, which is where blockchain comes into play. Here, financial transactions are meticulously recorded in the language of computer code."),
                            .text("When we say blockchain is distributed, it means that all parties engaged in a DeFi application possess an identical copy of this public ledger. It elegantly documents each transaction, concealing them in encrypted code. This not only ensures anonymity for users but also validates payments and maintains an unalterable record of asset ownership, effectively immune to fraudulent tampering."),
                            .text("Furthermore, the term \"decentralized\" emphasizes the absence of intermediaries or gatekeepers within the system. Transactions are authenticated and logged by parties utilizing the same blockchain, accomplished through the intricacies of solving complex mathematical puzzles and appending new transaction blocks to the chain. (4)"),
                            .text("Champions of DeFi ardently advocate that this decentralized blockchain architecture fortifies financial transactions, rendering them secure and more transparent than the private, opaque systems that dominate centralized finance. It's a transformation that heralds a new era of financial empowerment and transparency."),
                            .heading("🌷1.3 The Numbers_", level: 3),
                            .text("The endeavor to establish a financial system solely reliant on code and free from intermediaries has rapidly progressed. Over the last three years, this movement has witnessed a significant increase, with assets within this system surging from $4 billion to $104 billion. (6)"),
                            .text("More specifically, the DeFi sector has emerged as a dynamic industry, with a market capitalization surpassing $130 billion as of December 2021. This remarkable growth reflects a market that continuously expands its boundaries. Faced with this expansion, organizations must embark on a journey to understand the intricacies of DeFi technology, exploring the opportunities it presents while remaining mindful of the associated risks. This exploration is a crucial step in developing forward-thinking business strategies that enable organizations to establish a solid presence in the digital asset economy. (7)"),
                            .heading("🧶 1.4 Unraveling the Landscape_", level: 3),
                            .text("DeFi, an evolving convergence of blockchain, digital assets, and financial services, represents a transformative space. DeFi protocols are on a mission to revolutionize finance through a mix of both familiar and innovative service structures. "),
                            .callout(title: "About Ethereum", content: "Ethereum is both a crypto currency as well as actual blockchain. It is the infrastructure that allow other applications can be built upon. ", type: .tip),
                            .text("DeFi is an all-encompassing term that encapsulates a wide spectrum of activities and business relationships. Six principal DeFi service domains: stablecoins, exchanges, credit, derivatives, insurance, and asset management. In addition, auxiliary services such as wallets and oracles further enrich this multifaceted landscape. While traditional finance heavily relies on intermediaries to manage and facilitate financial services, DeFi operates within a decentralized realm—utilizing public, permissionless blockchains. Services are predominantly encoded within open-source software, comprising protocols and smart contracts."),
                            .text("Consider first having a fundamental understanding of blockchain technology is paramount, as DeFi operates on this foundation. Concepts such as public and private keys, transactions, confirmations, and consensus mechanisms like Proof of Stake or Proof of Work are vital to grasp. (8) "),
                            .callout(title: "PoW vs PoS", content: "The proof-of-work mechanism necessitates a substantial energy expenditure for transaction verification. Given that network computers must consume considerable energy and maintain high operational levels, blockchain technology is less environmentally sustainable compared to alternative systems. The primary concern associated with proof-of-stake lies in its substantial initial investment requirements. To become a validator, one must acquire a significant amount of the native cryptocurrency token, the quantity of which depends on the network's size. In practice, this can lead to a blockchain system that is predominantly controlled by affluent individuals or those with the financial capacity to amass a substantial stake in the network.", type: .info),
                            .text("Ensuring the security of your digital assets is a top priority. Learn about different types of wallets, including hardware, software, and paper wallets, and follow best practices for safeguarding private keys and recovery phrases. "),
                            .callout(title: "Wallet Security", content: "Wallets: Private key requirements. With DeFi and cryptocurrency, you must secure the wallets used to store your cryptocurrency assets. Wallets are secured with private keys, which are long, unique codes known only to the owner of the wallet. If you lose a private key, you lose access to your funds—there is no way to recover a lost private key.", type: .info),
                            .text("Recognize that DeFi investments come with inherent risks, including vulnerabilities in smart contracts, market volatility, and regulatory uncertainties. It's crucial to invest only what you can afford to lose, diversify your portfolio, and consider implementing risk management strategies. (9)"),
                            .text("Before engaging with a DeFi platform or investing in a project, check if they have undergone smart contract audits conducted by reputable third-party firms. These audits can help identify vulnerabilities and assess associated risks."),
                            .text("If you're new to DeFi, it's wise to start with small investments or transactions to gain experience and build confidence. As you become more acquainted with the ecosystem, you can gradually increase your exposure."),
                            .text("Be mindful of gas fees on blockchain networks like Ethereum, which cover transaction processing costs and can fluctuate significantly based on network congestion. Keep an eye on gas fees and explore the use of cost-effective layer 2 solutions for transactions."),
                            .text("Recognize that certain DeFi platforms may require you to provide personal information or undergo Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures, especially if you intend to interact with fiat onramps or centralized exchanges within the DeFi ecosystem. (world economic forum)"),
                            .text("Stay informed about regulatory developments in your jurisdiction, as some DeFi activities may be subject to specific regulations. Compliance is crucial to avoid legal complications."),
                            .text("Familiarize yourself with the user interfaces of the DeFi platforms you plan to use. Ensure that you understand how to utilize various features, such as providing liquidity, staking, and borrowing."),
                            .text("Establish proper backup and recovery mechanisms for your wallet and accounts. Losing access to your private keys or recovery phrases can result in permanent asset loss."),
                            .text("Consider potential tax implications associated with DeFi transactions, as tax obligations may vary by jurisdiction. Seeking guidance from a tax professional can help you understand and appropriately report crypto-related income. (10)"),
                            .text("Keep in mind that the DeFi space is continually evolving, with new projects and innovations emerging frequently. Staying informed, conducting thorough due diligence, and approaching the DeFi landscape with both caution and curiosity are essential for navigating it successfully."),
                            .callout(title: "Expand for Details", content: "Click on the Arrow to See More Info…", type: .info),
                            .text("DeFi leverages blockchain technology to provide alternatives to traditional service providers and market structures. It promises to foster innovation and the creation of new services that enhance the efficiency of financial markets. This aligns with ongoing advancements in financial technology (fintech) and the broader blockchain space. Whether it will fully realize these promises remains to be seen. (11)"),
                            .heading("🐫 1.5 The History_", level: 3),
                            .text("Throughout the history of financial markets, intermediaries have played pivotal roles as custodians of trust, liquidity providers, settlement facilitators, and security guarantors. Their roles have evolved and expanded to meet the demands of an increasingly complex financial landscape. However, the 2008 Global Financial Crisis and subsequent events have spotlighted inefficiencies, structural inequalities, and hidden risks within the intermediated financial system. Recent controversies have underscored additional shortcomings, including slow settlement cycles, price discovery inefficiencies, liquidity challenges, and uncertainty surrounding underlying assets. DeFi sets out to address some of these challenges, although several persist within the current DeFi ecosystem. (12) ")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_defi_3",
                        title: "2. The Stack_",
                        content: [
                            .text("Venturing into the world of DeFi (Decentralized Finance) can be an exhilarating journey, but it's paramount to be thoroughly prepared and well-informed due to the intricacies and risks involved. (13) Here are additional considerations and essential insights to bear in mind before immersing yourself in the depths of DeFi:"),
                            .text("DeFi represents a rapidly evolving landscape where new projects and innovations surface regularly. Staying well-informed, practicing due diligence, and embracing a prudent yet inquisitive mindset are your compass for successfully navigating the multifaceted realm of DeFi."),
                            .callout(title: "Smart Contracts", content: "Understanding Smart Contracts:", type: .info),
                            .heading("🎱 2.1 The Oracle: Fusion of External Information into DeFi_", level: 3),
                            .text("In the intricate web of DeFi transaction flows, external information and content have a pivotal role, which is facilitated by oracle services. These services act as conduits for dependable data that originates outside the blockchain's settlement layer. For instance, a price feed can seamlessly tap into external data sources and be autonomously delivered through a smart contract. It's important to note that these informational resources, along with the wallet software and user interfaces enabling the management, transfer, and storage of assets interfacing with DeFi services, fall into a distinct category. They are not, in themselves, classified as financial services but rather serve as auxiliary components within the DeFi ecosystem. (14)"),
                            .heading("♟️ 2.2 Layers_", level: 3),
                            .text("At its bedrock, the foundational layer comprises the blockchain system, a robust and secure platform. Here, participants are empowered to securely store, exchange, and modify ownership information related to assets. Remarkably, this blockchain layer seamlessly supplants the conventional financial services' execution and settlement functions. Additionally, it plays the crucial role of nurturing diverse forms of digital assets, providing the fertile ground from which these assets propagate into various DeFi applications."),
                            .callout(title: "Key Terms", content: "Need to Know Terms:", type: .info),
                            .text("Progressing up the stack, we encounter additional strata represented by application layers, functioning as adept aggregators. These aggregators bestow users with the invaluable flexibility to navigate effortlessly among various DeFi services. This adaptability ensures alignment with the ever-evolving real-time market dynamics. Within this dynamic ecosystem, digital assets are granted the liberty of unrestricted movement, facilitated by the governing contractual logic underpinning financial flows. Simultaneously, specific assets may be subject to constraints, serving either as collateral or furnishing liquidity through lock-up mechanisms. Extending beyond financial flows, there exists a parallel network of non-financial information exchange, bolstering the extensive tapestry of transactional activities within the dynamic realm of DeFi. (9)"),
                            .heading("🍇 2.3 Decentralized Governance and DAO: A Hidden Dimension_", level: 3),
                            .text("DeFi services may be made available to users through a variety of means. They might be offered by a traditional centralized entity, a community associated with a non-profit organization, or a decentralized autonomous organization (DAO). In the case of DAOs, rights and obligations are typically specified in smart contracts, ensuring decentralized and transparent governance. (15)"),
                            .text("This facet of the DeFi landscape is the implementation of decentralized governance mechanisms. Governance here pertains to the processes by which collective decisions are reached, conflicts are resolved, and protocol modifications are enacted. In the realm of DeFi, governance plays a pivotal role in mediating interactions between applications and the underlying settlement layer. These interactions encompass decisions ranging from adjusting interest rates to modifying collateral requirements."),
                            .callout(title: "Policy Questions", content: "This novel model raises a host of new questions for policy-makers and regulators, including inquiries such as:", type: .tip),
                            .text("Numerous DeFi projects incorporate a governance token, which bestows voting rights for specific governance decisions. Often, these tokens are traded on exchanges, their value intertwined with scarcity and the level of activity within the issuing DeFi service. Regulatory authorities must ascertain the appropriate classification for such tokens, discerning whether they are primarily employed for governance or serve as proxies for investments in the service. Governance may be partially decentralized, with token holders exercising limited voting rights, while developers may retain effective veto power through substantial token holdings, or they may have no formal obligation to enact proposed changes. In certain instances of partial decentralization, individuals are designated to execute changes based on token holder votes. This is done through multi-sign keys, which require multiple signatures from delegates to implement alterations. (16)"),
                            .text("In the realm of decentralized governance, decision-making shifts entirely to a community of token holders through the establishment of a Decentralized Autonomous Organization (DAO). Participants in the DAO cast votes on protocol changes, aligned through token incentives and governed by rules enshrined in smart contracts. Governance decisions are enacted as blockchain transactions, enforced through the consensus mechanisms of the settlement layer.\n"),
                            .text("Source: Wharton Blockchain and Digital Asset Project, in collaboration with the World Economic Forum")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_defi_4",
                        title: "3. Digital Assets_",
                        content: [
                            .text("Digital assets come in a variety of forms. We will briefly touch here on the different varieties. Please be aware that due to the technology, it is constantly changing…"),
                            .heading("🍭 3.1 Currency vs. Tokens", level: 3),
                            .text("Cryptocurrencies and tokens are both digital assets, but they serve different purposes and have distinct characteristics. Here's a breakdown of the key differences between cryptocurrencies and tokens, along with examples of each: (17) "),
                            .text("Cryptocurrencies:"),
                            .callout(title: "Crypto Examples", content: "Examples: Some well-known cryptocurrencies include:", type: .tip),
                            .text("Tokens:"),
                            .callout(title: "Token Types", content: "Examples: There are various types of tokens, including:", type: .tip),
                            .text("Basically, cryptocurrencies are standalone digital currencies that operate on their own blockchains and are primarily used for financial transactions. Tokens, on the other hand, are created on existing blockchains and serve various purposes, from providing access to platforms and services to representing ownership of assets or unique digital items. (18) The key distinction is that tokens rely on the infrastructure of a blockchain, while cryptocurrencies have their independent blockchains."),
                            .callout(title: "NFT Wiki", content: "Transport yourself to the NFT Wiki for comprehensive information on non-fungible tokens.", type: .link),
                            .heading("🏛️ 3.2 Exploring the Stability of Stablecoins_", level: 3),
                            .text("Stablecoins, a fundamental component of the DeFi landscape, are designed with a singular mission: to retain a consistent value of a token in relation to a chosen asset, typically the U.S. dollar or other prominent fiat currencies. Theoretically, $1 = 1 Token."),
                            .callout(title: "Fiat Currency", content: "Fiat aka Money ", type: .tip),
                            .text("These digital assets provide a valuable bridge between the crypto world's volatility and the stability sought after in traditional financial systems. (19) Dive deeper into the diverse facets of stablecoins:"),
                            .text("Stablecoins, with their commitment to price stability and utility within the DeFi ecosystem, continue to evolve and shape the financial landscape by offering a reliable and seamless medium for participants in both the traditional and crypto financial realms."),
                            .heading("🧭 3.3 DeFi vs. CBDC: The Distinctions_", level: 3),
                            .text("DeFi (Decentralized Finance) and CBDC (Central Bank Digital Currency) emerge as two distinct pillars within the domain of digital currencies and finance, each weaving its narrative of characteristics and objectives. Let's embark on a journey to discern the key disparities between DeFi and CBDC:"),
                            .comparisonTable(title: "DeFi vs. CBDC", items: [
                                ComparisonItem(label: "Authority & Issuance", values: [
                                    "Decentralized, operating under governance of code on blockchains like Ethereum, untouched by central authorities.",
                                    "Digital currencies created and regulated by central banks, bearing full government endorsement as sovereign currency."
                                ]),
                                ComparisonItem(label: "Centralization", values: [
                                    "Fully decentralized architecture with no single point of control; governed by distributed consensus mechanisms and community governance.",
                                    "Centralized digital renditions of a nation's fiat currency, overseen and regulated by central banks."
                                ]),
                                ComparisonItem(label: "Regulation", values: [
                                    "Platforms navigate regulatory gray areas, potentially not conforming to conventional institutional standards of oversight.",
                                    "Subject to rigorous regulatory scrutiny and adherence to financial statutes within their jurisdiction."
                                ]),
                                ComparisonItem(label: "Stability & Value", values: [
                                    "Assets including crypto and tokens experience volatile market forces and significant value oscillations.",
                                    "Purposefully designed for steady value, tethered to national fiat currency, targeting price stability."
                                ]),
                                ComparisonItem(label: "Access & Inclusivity", values: [
                                    "Grants financial services access to anyone with internet and a digital wallet, including unbanked populations.",
                                    "Bolster financial inclusion by extending digital currency access to a broader populace."
                                ]),
                                ComparisonItem(label: "Privacy & Security", values: [
                                    "Pseudonymous transactions on public blockchains; users maintain custody of private keys.",
                                    "Engineered with configurable privacy and traceability options shaped by central bank policy."
                                ]),
                                ComparisonItem(label: "Use Cases", values: [
                                    "Alternative permissionless financial ecosystem: lending, borrowing, trading, yield farming outside traditional banking.",
                                    "Refining monetary infrastructure efficiency, cross-border transactions, reducing cash reliance, controlling money supply."
                                ])
                            ]),
                            .text("In essence, DeFi and CBDCs represent disparate pathways in the realm of digital currency and finance. DeFi champions decentralization, openness, and blockchain technology, while CBDCs emerge as centralized digital avatars of a nation's fiat currency, overseen and regulated by central banks. Their missions, governance models, regulatory landscapes, and implications for the financial arena embody stark differences. (20) "),
                            .heading("🗻 3.4 Striving for Stability in DeFi", level: 3),
                            .text("Ensuring stability in the dynamic realm of DeFi (Decentralized Finance) is an ongoing challenge due to the inherent volatility of many DeFi assets. (21) However, the DeFi community has been diligently exploring various methods and mechanisms to address this concern and promote stability. Here are some of the most promising approaches:"),
                            .text("It's worth emphasizing that while these mechanisms hold promise, the world of DeFi remains experimental and rapidly evolving, offering no guarantees of stability. Users should diligently research, comprehend the associated risks, and exercise caution when engaging in DeFi activities. Additionally, the efficacy of these stability mechanisms is influenced by a range of factors, including market dynamics and the unique design of each DeFi project.")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_defi_5",
                        title: "4. Defining Traits_",
                        content: [
                            .text("Not every instance of blockchain technology implementation, even those entailing financial transactions, can be baptized as DeFi. Similarly, not every cog that churns within the machinery of the DeFi ecosystem rightfully earns the badge of a DeFi service, enterprise, or software protocol. As the landscape continually mutates, it unfurls a set of distinct characteristic."),
                            .heading("🌿 4.1 Within Financial Services_", level: 3),
                            .text("DeFi finds its footing in the realm of directly facilitating the transmission and interchange of value. While auxiliary services such as oracles, query systems, and decentralized storage may emerge as pivotal enablers of DeFi activities, it remains imperative to distinguish them from DeFi services per se."),
                            .heading("🌵 4.2 Trust-Minimized Operation and Settlement_", level: 3),
                            .text("DeFi ventures predominantly find their abode on public, permissionless blockchains embedded with the functionality of smart contracts, much like the venerated Ethereum. Transactions gracefully pirouette to the tunes of DeFi protocols, orchestrating executions and recordings in harmony with these protocols' stipulated rules. The realm of trust minimization often extends to the governance frameworks orchestrating the conditions conducive for protocol metamorphosis."),
                            .heading("🌳 4.3 Non-Custodial Design_", level: 3),
                            .text("The assets entrusted under the aegis of DeFi services, theoretically, remain untouchable by third-party interlopers. The core ethos of DeFi is user-centric, endowing patrons with unswerving dominion. Consequently, centralized cryptocurrency exchanges clutching digital assets in their custodial grip do not qualify as DeFi entities, notwithstanding their forays into developing DeFi derivatives."),
                            .heading("🌴 4.4 Open, Programmable, and Composable Architecture_", level: 3),
                            .text("DeFi's underlying source code basks in open accessibility, while a publicly accessible application programming interface (API) paves the way for integration. This holistic composition orchestrates a vibrant symphony, whereby components find themselves interwoven, designed to spawn fresh financial instruments and services dynamically. For instance, a stablecoin may metamorphose into the cornerstone of a derivative, which, in turn, takes up the mantle as collateral for a loan, all while being encapsulated by an insurance contract."),
                            .heading("🍃 4.5 Survey: Order of Magnitude_", level: 3),
                            .text("In a survey about the biggest pain points with DeFi for operators within the space the term “order of magnitude” came up…  "),
                            .text("Observations from our Open Survey:"),
                            .text("Order of Magnitude More Efficient and Transparent:"),
                            .text("Order of Magnitude More Transparently could Equal Scams:"),
                            .text("In essence, these phrases highlight the double-edged nature of DeFi. On one hand, it offers efficiency and transparency in financial transactions, reducing reliance on traditional financial institutions. On the other hand, the openness of the ecosystem can make it easier for bad actors to operate scams, requiring users to exercise caution and conduct thorough research before participating in DeFi projects."),
                            .heading("🍏 4.6 DeFi vs. Traditional Finance: The Smart Contract Paradigm", level: 3),
                            .text("When delving into the distinction between DeFi and traditional finance, the introduction of smart contracts aimed to revolutionize the financial service industry by offering a completely automated approach. Essentially, programmability equates to reliability. This foundational concept underpinning smart contracts is undoubtedly appealing in theory. While some may argue the merits of humans versus machines, it is crucial for users and investors to recognize that there exists a time and place for both approaches."),
                            .heading("“Many DeFi fans argue that blockchains are technologically superior to the existing banking system, much of which runs on ancient databases and outdated code. (Most bank transactions, for example, still rely on programs written in COBOL, a programming language that dates back to the 1960s.) Crypto, they say, is the first form of money that is actually devised for the internet, and as it grows, it will need a new, internet-native financial system to support it.” ", level: 3),
                            .text("Engaging with a financial advisor, coupled with a solid understanding of the fundamentals of decentralized finance, the inner workings of a smart contract, and the key players in the field, significantly enriches the ability to diversify your investment portfolio. (23) It also equips you to navigate the path toward long-term wealth creation by leveraging the available technologies when and where they best serve your financial goals.")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_defi_6",
                        title: "5. Risk_",
                        content: [
                            .text("Since this entire endeavor is incredibly new, the innovations are constantly changing. As you are looking to invest, please recognize the risk involved. It honestly would be more of an investment in the future and less of an investment of straight ROI."),
                            .callout(title: "Deep Dive", content: "Dive Into: An Unapologetically High-Risk Dive into DeFi Emulating Institutional Financial Services...", type: .explore)
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_defi_7",
                        title: "6. Making Headway into the Future_",
                        content: [
                            .text("Decentralized Finance, presents a direct challenge to the conventional centralized financial system. It achieves this by diminishing the influence of intermediaries and gatekeepers while empowering everyday individuals through peer-to-peer transactions. It takes the fundamental functions performed by banks, exchanges, and insurers, such as lending, borrowing, and trading, and places these capabilities into the hands of regular people. "),
                            .callout(title: "Current Work", content: "Currently in the endeavors of creating new ways of economic ownership.", type: .info),
                            .text("The mainstream adoption of cryptocurrency has ignited a remarkably divided discussion. Ardent supporters view it as a savior of the world, while staunch skeptics are resolutely convinced it's a fraudulent endeavor – a speculative bubble with detrimental environmental impacts, masterminded by deceitful individuals and marketed to avaricious individuals. They fear its eventual burst could have severe economic repercussions."),
                            .text("Investors are on the verge of gaining unprecedented autonomy, enabling them to explore creative and seemingly impossible ways of deploying their assets. DeFi's maturation also holds substantial implications for the big data sector, as it paves the way for innovative approaches to data commodification."),
                            .text("DeFi still faces substantial challenges, particularly in terms of widespread adoption by the general public. Regardless, Decentralized Finance is here to stay…"),
                            .divider,
                            .callout(title: "Legal Disclaimer", content: "*Legally we recommend you work with your financial advisor, as Untitled_ does not offer financial advice or have a FINRA license. ", type: .info),
                            .divider,
                            .text("Copyright 2023 by Untitled_ Lux Perpetua Technologies Inc. IP Patents Pending")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    )
