                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_art_6",
                        title: "5. Chance and Observational Inquiry_",
                        content: [
                            .heading("🧊 5.1 Rare Art Moments where Chance Ruled", level: 3),
                            .text("The sales of Damien Hirst's Spot paintings over the past five years reveals significant fluctuations. For instance, a Damien Hirst Spot painting valued at $450,000 in 2003 might have commanded a price exceeding $1.5 million by 2007 due to the thriving Contemporary art market during that period. These examples illustrate how shifts in both artistic taste and the broader economic landscape can lead to dramatic changes in the value of artworks. (20)"),
                            .heading("🏛️ 5.2 Observational Inquiry_", level: 3),
                            .text("Art investing is a communal effort. It is an asset class that is more inline with the unsaid and the obvious. Beyond the spreadsheet investing in art is a choice that allows for passions and interests to do much of the investing, yielding actual financial returns as well. "),
                            .text("Many artworks truly come to life when experienced in person. The distinctive allure, character, and subtle nuances become fully evident during such encounters."),
                            .text("We at Untitled_ invite you, the next time you are in a gallery and/or museum to strike up a conversation with a fellow patron. In part, it helps shape the market space for a richer, more equitable future. Second, it builds confidence and sparks a certain joy. Have you ever heard someone explain to you why they love a specific painting? Usually, no matter their background, there is a spark in their eye. Passion is the driver of this investment thesis. "),
                            .callout(title: "Investor Mindset", content: "I must learn that as an investor my credibility lies with me, my instincts and my observations. ", type: .info),
                            .text("Like any other investment thesis or strategy, art has its own market signifiers. Like a hedge fund manager who can see the relation between the inflation rates of the Yen and can hedge the Euro, similarly there are unique markers in the art market. But first, you must understand the importance of Observation. "),
                            .text("Most outsiders think art is based in fantasy, the minds eye or a realm that only the artist can access. In contrast, the extremely and sometimes difficult truth, is that creativity is grounded in reality, in the particular, the focused and well observed. Possibly the specifically imagined. ")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
