                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_art_7",
                        title: "6. Ethics and Assessments",
                        content: [
                            .text("Historically high art has been at the basis of cultural appropriation, looting, war and white collar crimes. Museums such as The Metropolitan Museum of Art, Tate Britain, other dealers and collectors have found themselves in the face of ethical dilemmas. "),
                            .heading("🫁 6.1 Historical States of Undoing_", level: 3),
                            .text("Many of these involved works stolen and/or pillaged. The Gurlitt Collection was a trove of art discovered in the Munich apartment of Cornelius Gurlitt, the son of an art dealer who had dealings with the Nazis during World War II. The collection included works by artists such as Picasso, Matisse, and Chagall. The ownership of many of these artworks came into question due to suspicions of Nazi looting and forced sales. Subsequent legal battles ensued over the rightful ownership of the pieces. (22)"),
                            .text("A legal battle emerged over a Modigliani painting, \"Seated Man With a Cane,\" which was alleged to have been stolen by the Nazis during World War II. The dispute revolved around whether the current owner should be required to return the painting to the heirs of the original Jewish owner, who had been forced to sell it under duress. (23)"),
                            .text("After the artist’s death, the works of Andy Warhol were set up to be authenticated by The Andy Warhol Authentication Board, established in 1995, to create a supposed streamlined process to provide reliable and expert opinion on the authenticity of the artworks attributed to Warhol. Remember, he produced out of The Factory, so many works were created by him, but also had many hands touching the process. While created in good faith it actually ran into several controversies and legal challenges during its existence. Some art owners and collectors disagreed with the board's determinations and argued that their artworks were authentic Warhols. The board's practice of not providing detailed explanations for rejections led to frustration and legal disputes. Art owners believed they were entitled to know why their works were deemed inauthentic. Legal challenges then often revolved around claims of defamation and interference with potential sales. Art owners who had their works rejected by the board felt that the rejections harmed the value and reputation of their pieces. Today, the authentication of Warhol's artworks is carried out by various experts, institutions, and scholars who use a combination of documentation, expertise, and connoisseurship to determine authenticity. (24)"),
                            .text("Another instance, a Picasso painting, such as the Portrait of Angel Fernandez de Soto, originally expected to fetch between $40 million and $60 million, was removed from a Christie's auction in 2006 due to a purported ownership dispute."),
                            .text("Needless to say, it is important to have a full understanding of the notoriety within proper ownership and track record. With this, the legal dimensions of the appraisal profession have assumed a paramount role. At its most advanced levels, appraisal demands a profound understanding of critical issues, including but not limited to, establishing clear title (frequently compromised by stolen and looted art), familiarity with the legal framework safeguarding cultural property, IRS regulations, authentication determinations, selecting the appropriate market (retail and tax shelters), assessing volume discounts, navigating the interplay between case law and the Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice (USPAP), and the legal aspects related to appraising damage and loss. (25) This is especially true for modern and contemporary art artists such as O’Keeffe, Rothko, Warhol and Calder."),
                            .text("Between conceptual art and digital art, it is even more difficult to asses the authenticity of a work. In the realm of conceptual art, assessing value can be somewhat challenging, especially given the absence of standardized criteria. This complexity often arises from the utilization of unconventional materials and, in cases where the artist is still alive, the need for a nuanced evaluation of the underlying asset. (26)"),
                            .text("The rise of digital within the art community, most particularly the reproduction of existing media, reproduced with a slight differentiation by an artist or the rise of AI artwork, traditional artwork appraisal and authentication will change with the art movements as well."),
                            .callout(title: "Note", content: "Additional information available in related modules.", type: .info)
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
                        level: 2,
                        reflectionPrompts: [],
                        glossaryTerms: [],
                        relatedResearch: []
                    ),
                    Section(
                        id: "sec_mod_art_8",
                        title: "7. Into the Deep_",
                        content: [
                            .text("Art investing, whether it be in the form of an art fund, portfolio mix, or for educational curiosities, is a gateway into the alternative investing universe. It serves as a dynamic channel through which investors can access a multifaceted realm of opportunities. Here's an expansion on why art investment serves as an entry point to the diverse world of alternative investments."),
                            .heading("🧊 7.1 Dive Right In_", level: 3),
                            .text("The underlying aspiration of this module is to empower you with the right set of tools and assessments, allowing you to venture further along your path of portfolio diversification. This journey may encompass the inclusion of art assets as a viable and rewarding option. Nevertheless, it is imperative that you maintain open lines of communication with your financial advisor, who can offer personalized guidance tailored to your unique financial situation."),
                            .text("It's crucial to reiterate that this module isn't about securing exclusive access or first opportunities; instead, it is geared toward the overarching goal of diversification. It aims to serve as your guide, a navigational aid for what might initially seem like a complex and intricate landscape. The operative word here is \"seemingly.\" It's pivotal to recognize and remind yourself that you indeed possess the determination, intellect, and unwavering determination to engage in investment strategies that best align with your financial objectives and aspirations. Always keep this in mind as you embark on your investment journey, knowing that with the right tools and the backing of sound financial advice, you are well-equipped to navigate this intricate terrain and make informed choices."),
                            .divider,
                            .callout(title: "Legal Disclaimer", content: "*Legally we recommend you work with your financial advisor, as Untitled_ does not offer financial advice or have a FINRA license. Untitled_ operates under SEC 506c and Reg A Blue Sky Laws. Again, Please speak with your financial advisor before making investment decisions. Past performance does not indicate future performance. ", type: .info),
                            .divider,
                            .text("Copyright 2023 by Untitled_ LuxPerpetua Technologies Inc. along with Victoria Case. IP Patents Pending")
                        ],
                        isCollapsible: true,
